message.entry: TXSIG and RXSIG must be the same dimensions.
''msk/diff'' is equivalent to ''msk'' and ''msk/nondiff'' is equivalent to\n''msk/precoded''. ''msk/diff'' and ''msk/nondiff'' are obsolete options. Please use\n''msk'' or ''msk/precoded'' instead.
For MSK modulation, the signals must be at least 4 symbols long.
Nsamp must be a real, positive integer scalar.
EbNo must be a real vector.
NUM must be a numeric vector.
DEN must be a numeric vector.
TXSIG must be a complex vector.
RXSIG must be a complex vector.
For PSK modulation with differential encoding, M must be 2 or 4.
For PSK modulation with nondifferential encoding, M must be 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, or 64.
For QAM modulation, M must be an integer power of 2 between 4 and 1024, inclusive.
For DPSK modulation, M must be 2 or 4.
For OQPSK modulation, M must be 4.
For MSK modulation, M must be 2.
